Alec Baldwin and director James Toback's documentary Seduced and Abandoned gives an insight into the 
The film was shot at Cannes last year: cameras trailed Baldwin and Toback as they met key players in the movie business to discuss and get funding for a far-fetched film project.The documentary features conversations with Hollywood heavyweights Martin Scorsese, Francis Ford Coppola and actor Ryan Gosling and is an oddly moving exposé of the industry’s machinations, says the BBC’s Tom Brook.If you would like to comment on this story or anything else you have seen on BBC Culture, head over to ourFacebookpage or message us onTwitter.You can also find Talking Movies onFacebook.